00:00:48.650 --> 00:00:51.510 align:middle line:84%
There have been some really
big shockers in the series.

00:00:51.510 --> 00:00:54.840 align:middle line:84%
And, sadly, this is also true
in real life as people commonly

00:00:54.840 --> 00:00:57.300 align:middle line:84%
make the wrong
assumptions about divorce

00:00:57.300 --> 00:01:01.260 align:middle line:84%
and, in particular, how your
finances stand to be split.

00:01:01.260 --> 00:01:03.330 align:middle line:84%
Joining me to discuss
is Lucy Warwick-Ching,

00:01:03.330 --> 00:01:04.920 align:middle line:90%
FT Money's digital editor.

00:01:04.920 --> 00:01:05.840 align:middle line:90%
Welcome, Lucy.

00:01:05.840 --> 00:01:06.470 align:middle line:90%
Hello.

00:01:06.470 --> 00:01:10.350 align:middle line:84%
Well, this got a
roaring response online,

00:01:10.350 --> 00:01:12.540 align:middle line:84%
not least because many of
the most powerful myths

00:01:12.540 --> 00:01:15.240 align:middle line:90%
about divorce concern adultery.

00:01:15.240 --> 00:01:16.350 align:middle line:90%
Tell me more.

00:01:16.350 --> 00:01:19.680 align:middle line:84%
Yes, that is the key word
that got people commenting

00:01:19.680 --> 00:01:20.820 align:middle line:90%
and reading the piece.

00:01:20.820 --> 00:01:23.660 align:middle line:84%
But there are some other
great myths in there, as well.

00:01:23.660 --> 00:01:26.310 align:middle line:84%
But, so, on the
topic of adultery.

00:01:26.310 --> 00:01:29.815 align:middle line:84%
So people often think that
because their partner has

00:01:29.815 --> 00:01:32.190 align:middle line:84%
committed adultery or they've
had an affair with somebody

00:01:32.190 --> 00:01:34.890 align:middle line:84%
else, it's hurt them
very deeply and it's

00:01:34.890 --> 00:01:37.557 align:middle line:84%
very key to their
feeling that they often

00:01:37.557 --> 00:01:40.140 align:middle line:84%
think that they're going to get
a bigger financial settlement.

00:01:40.140 --> 00:01:41.760 align:middle line:84%
But actually, this
isn't the case.

00:01:41.760 --> 00:01:44.490 align:middle line:84%
The courts recognise that
marriages break down.

00:01:44.490 --> 00:01:46.380 align:middle line:84%
And what the courts
are more interested in

00:01:46.380 --> 00:01:48.870 align:middle line:84%
is what resources you
each have available

00:01:48.870 --> 00:01:51.100 align:middle line:84%
and how they are to
be divided fairly.

00:01:51.100 --> 00:01:54.540 align:middle line:84%
So, unfortunately, if your
partner commits adultery

00:01:54.540 --> 00:01:57.540 align:middle line:84%
or behaves unreasonably,
you won't automatically

00:01:57.540 --> 00:02:00.570 align:middle line:84%
get a bigger settlement
for them to be--

00:02:00.570 --> 00:02:03.000 align:middle line:84%
for you to get a more
advantageous one,

00:02:03.000 --> 00:02:06.720 align:middle line:84%
you have to actually look at how
the party's behaviour has had

00:02:06.720 --> 00:02:09.930 align:middle line:84%
an impact on your
relationship, and file for kind

00:02:09.930 --> 00:02:11.460 align:middle line:90%
of unreasonable behaviour.

00:02:11.460 --> 00:02:13.410 align:middle line:84%
So that surprises
lots of people.

00:02:13.410 --> 00:02:15.630 align:middle line:84%
But while we're on the
subject of adultery,

00:02:15.630 --> 00:02:17.580 align:middle line:84%
the actual legal
definition rests

00:02:17.580 --> 00:02:21.570 align:middle line:84%
on this being committed with
a member of the opposite sex.

00:02:21.570 --> 00:02:22.080 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:02:22.080 --> 00:02:24.830 align:middle line:84%
This surprised everybody
that I mentioned it to.

00:02:24.830 --> 00:02:26.970 align:middle line:84%
It had people talking
about it in the office

00:02:26.970 --> 00:02:28.260 align:middle line:90%
and disagreeing about it.

00:02:28.260 --> 00:02:30.420 align:middle line:84%
So I had to really go
back to the lawyers

00:02:30.420 --> 00:02:32.310 align:middle line:90%
and really check this one out.

00:02:32.310 --> 00:02:34.290 align:middle line:84%
It's one of those
archaic English laws

00:02:34.290 --> 00:02:37.950 align:middle line:84%
that many believe to be-- quite
rightly so-- discriminatory.

00:02:37.950 --> 00:02:41.910 align:middle line:84%
But the way the English law
works at the moment is that it

00:02:41.910 --> 00:02:45.450 align:middle line:84%
only recognises adultery
between a man and a woman.

00:02:45.450 --> 00:02:49.950 align:middle line:84%
That said, the courts may
actually be sympathetic

00:02:49.950 --> 00:02:52.470 align:middle line:84%
because they do understand
that relationships

00:02:52.470 --> 00:02:55.170 align:middle line:84%
happen between lots
of different people.

00:02:55.170 --> 00:02:59.490 align:middle line:84%
And so if you take it to the
court and the judge looks

00:02:59.490 --> 00:03:02.790 align:middle line:84%
at your case, then they may
deem it to be unreasonable

00:03:02.790 --> 00:03:03.450 align:middle line:90%
behaviour.

00:03:03.450 --> 00:03:05.700 align:middle line:84%
So you won't automatically
be able to file for grounds

00:03:05.700 --> 00:03:07.530 align:middle line:84%
for divorce when
adultery is committed

00:03:07.530 --> 00:03:09.134 align:middle line:90%
with a member of the same sex.

00:03:09.134 --> 00:03:10.800 align:middle line:84%
Well, thanks for
clearing that up, Lucy.

00:03:10.800 --> 00:03:12.830 align:middle line:84%
But the article you
wrote on FT Money

00:03:12.830 --> 00:03:14.310 align:middle line:90%
cites the 10 most common myths.

00:03:14.310 --> 00:03:15.784 align:middle line:84%
And we've dealt
with two of them.

00:03:15.784 --> 00:03:16.950 align:middle line:90%
Read the piece for the rest.

00:03:16.950 --> 00:03:19.560 align:middle line:84%
But you also go into
another worrying aspect,

00:03:19.560 --> 00:03:22.470 align:middle line:84%
that divorcing couples
often don't think of.

00:03:22.470 --> 00:03:25.300 align:middle line:90%
Namely, their cybersecurity.

00:03:25.300 --> 00:03:28.400 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, many people share their
passwords with their spouses.

00:03:28.400 --> 00:03:31.140 align:middle line:84%
And then when everything's rosy
and the relationship is going

00:03:31.140 --> 00:03:33.630 align:middle line:90%
really well, this is fine.

00:03:33.630 --> 00:03:35.610 align:middle line:84%
But, actually,
they kind of forget

00:03:35.610 --> 00:03:37.170 align:middle line:84%
that when things
are going wrong,

00:03:37.170 --> 00:03:41.160 align:middle line:84%
that actually it's very
easy with devices these days

00:03:41.160 --> 00:03:44.820 align:middle line:84%
to look at something that your
partner has sent because it

00:03:44.820 --> 00:03:46.065 align:middle line:90%
may pop up on the screen.

00:03:46.065 --> 00:03:49.110 align:middle line:84%
Or in some cases,
high profile cases,

00:03:49.110 --> 00:03:51.990 align:middle line:84%
there's been examples
of where affairs

00:03:51.990 --> 00:03:54.930 align:middle line:84%
have come to light
because one partner sent

00:03:54.930 --> 00:03:57.780 align:middle line:84%
a text to the person they're
having an affair with

00:03:57.780 --> 00:04:00.095 align:middle line:84%
and it's popped up
on the family iPad.

00:04:00.095 --> 00:04:00.900 align:middle line:90%
Good grief!

00:04:00.900 --> 00:04:02.050 align:middle line:90%
And so yes.

00:04:02.050 --> 00:04:03.050 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:04:03.050 --> 00:04:06.720 align:middle line:84%
So it's much more
important to not leave

00:04:06.720 --> 00:04:08.860 align:middle line:90%
yourself exposed online.

00:04:08.860 --> 00:04:11.040 align:middle line:84%
And one of the things
that really surprised

00:04:11.040 --> 00:04:13.560 align:middle line:84%
me was that people
could see e-mails,

00:04:13.560 --> 00:04:15.060 align:middle line:84%
you know, from your
divorce lawyer.

00:04:15.060 --> 00:04:19.019 align:middle line:84%
One was saying she had found
out because a password hadn't

00:04:19.019 --> 00:04:19.839 align:middle line:90%
been changed.

00:04:19.839 --> 00:04:20.339 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:04:20.339 --> 00:04:20.838 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:04:20.838 --> 00:04:22.820 align:middle line:84%
But the thing to
be said actually

00:04:22.820 --> 00:04:24.590 align:middle line:90%
is don't be tempted to spy.

00:04:24.590 --> 00:04:28.290 align:middle line:84%
So although you may have access
to your partner's e-mails

00:04:28.290 --> 00:04:33.060 align:middle line:84%
or you may be able to log into
their WhatsApp or anything,

00:04:33.060 --> 00:04:36.904 align:middle line:84%
it's illegal to actually
access your partner's details.

00:04:36.904 --> 00:04:38.820 align:middle line:84%
You know, I mean, that--
that's quite obvious.

00:04:38.820 --> 00:04:42.050 align:middle line:84%
But it may be that people
might not really know about it.

00:04:42.050 --> 00:04:44.400 align:middle line:84%
And, actually, if you
do come across something

00:04:44.400 --> 00:04:47.910 align:middle line:84%
that you found in your
partner's online accounts, then

00:04:47.910 --> 00:04:50.970 align:middle line:84%
you won't be able to use
this in law against them.

00:04:50.970 --> 00:04:54.241 align:middle line:84%
And you also may end up with
a prison sentence or a fine.

00:04:54.241 --> 00:04:56.490 align:middle line:84%
Well, thank you very much
there to Lucy Warwick-Ching.

00:04:56.490 --> 00:04:58.840 align:middle line:84%
You can read her full
report online now,

